msgid "Composing a correct MFT header automagically"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:430
msgid "The first step in getting Gnus to automagically generate a MFT header in posts you make is to give Gnus a list of the mailing lists addresses you are subscribed to.  You can do this in more than one way.  The following variables would come in handy."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:433
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:434
#, no-wrap
msgid "message-subscribed-addresses"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:437
msgid "This should be a list of addresses the user is subscribed to.  Its default value is @code{nil}.  Example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:440
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq message-subscribed-addresses\n"
"      '(\"ding@@gnus.org\" \"bing@@noose.org\"))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:442
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "message-subscribed-regexps"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:447
msgid "This should be a list of regexps denoting the addresses of mailing lists subscribed to.  Default value is @code{nil}.  Example: If you want to achieve the same result as above:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq message-subscribed-regexps\n"
"      '(\"\\\\(ding@@gnus\\\\)\\\\|\\\\(bing@@noose\\\\)\\\\.org\")\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:452
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:453
#, no-wrap
msgid "message-subscribed-address-functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:457
msgid "This can be a list of functions to be called (one at a time!!) to determine the value of MFT headers.  It is advisable that these functions not take any arguments.  Default value is @code{nil}."
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:464
msgid "There is a pre-defined function in Gnus that is a good candidate for this variable.  @code{gnus-find-subscribed-addresses} is a function that returns a list of addresses corresponding to the groups that have the @code{subscribed} (@pxref{Group Parameters, ,Group Parameters, gnus, The Gnus Manual}) group parameter set to a non-@code{nil} value.  This is how you would do it."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq message-subscribed-address-functions\n"
"      '(gnus-find-subscribed-addresses))\n"
msgstr ""

