#. type: Plain text
#: ../../../../../doc/misc/message.texi:1278
msgid "If you have imported your old PGP 2.x key into GnuPG, and want to send signed and encrypted messages to your fellow PGP 2.x users, you'll discover that the receiver cannot understand what you send. One solution is to use PGP 2.x instead (e.g., if you use @code{pgg}, set @code{pgg-default-scheme} to @code{pgp}). You could also convince your fellow PGP 2.x users to convert to GnuPG@."
